    <prp:abstract>Our proposal aims at observing the dust and molecular gas content, distribution, and dynamics as traced by the CO(1-0) line and continuum emission of the intriguing NGC5719 merging galaxy with extended decoupled stellar disks. Thanks to the superb angular resolution (1arcsec, or 100pc, the typical size of giant molecular clouds) and sensitivity achievable with Band 4, we sample the central 7arcmin x 1arcmin region complementing the knowledge of the ISM physical conditions and kinematics obtained from  resolved (optical and radio) line images of this system. 

These observations will allow us to discuss the effects of an on-going acquisition event in the framework of the origin of counter-rotating stellar disks.
</prp:abstract>
